  "description": "Gottsclialk Johan Olof Erasmie was a Swedish district surveyor born on March 16, 1906, in Herrljunga, Älvsborg county. He was the son of post office assistant Ivar E. and Anna Ekelund. He married Marigarete Benter in 1930, and they had four children. Erasmie graduated from Skara with a bachelor's degree in 1924 and later received his land surveyor's certification in 1928 and took a cultural technology course in 1933. He worked as a surveyor in several counties and districts in Sweden, including Kalmar, Uppsala, Jämtland, Ströms, and Skara. He was a member of the Strömsund municipal council from 1942-1946 and served as chairman of the housing committee in 1944. Since 1947, he has been a surveyor in Kvänum and Lundbybrunn municipal associations. " 
